20/05/2008
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Prosecutor-General Boris Velchev confirmed on Monday (May 19th) that he plans to ask parliament to lift the immunity member Rumen Petkov enjoys. Petkov returned to parliament after stepping down as interior minister recently amid a scandal involving information being leaked from the ministry to crime bosses. During the scandal, Petkov revealed the identity of a police official working undercover for the National Security Agency, which is punishable by up to five years in prison. (Dnevnik, 24 chasa, Trud, Sega - 20/05/08; Mediapool, bTV, BNT - 19/05/08)
